---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Research - Martin Lukac">
  <Navbar />
  
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20 px-4 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-container-narrow mx-auto relative z-10">
      <h1 class="text-h2 text-text-primary mb-20">Research</h1>

      <!-- Philosophy Section: Neutral/Calm -->
      <section class="section-padding" data-particle-color="#6B7785" data-particle-speed="0.5">
        <p class="text-body-large text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-16 max-w-3xl">
          My research philosophy centers on the <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">rigorous deployment of AI in high-stakes environments</span>. Whether automating legal workflows at <span class="text-flank font-medium">Flank</span> or supporting mental health at <span class="text-sentra font-medium">Sentra</span>, I believe that safety and reliability are not afterthoughts but core design constraints.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <!-- Flank: Red/Active -->
          <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-border" data-particle-color="#E27B7B" data-particle-speed="2">
            <h3 class="text-h4 text-text-primary mb-4">Agentic Reliability</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Moving beyond stochastic outputs to auditable, protocol-driven actions. In legal tech, this means ensuring agents can handle objections and draft documents with precision and traceability.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Sentra: Blue/Steady -->
          <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-border" data-particle-color="#4A90E2" data-particle-speed="1">
            <h3 class="text-h4 text-text-primary mb-4">Safety in Practice</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Implementing concrete guardrails for vulnerability and risk. For <span class="text-sentra font-medium">Sentra</span> and <span class="text-psysafe font-medium">PsySafe</span>, this involves detecting crisis signals and ensuring safe handoffs, bridging the gap between theoretical alignment and clinical reality.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Societal: Green/Slow -->
          <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl border border-border md:col-span-2" data-particle-color="#7EC699" data-particle-speed="0.3">
            <h3 class="text-h4 text-text-primary mb-4">Societal Impact</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Grounded in my background in computational social science, I study how these deployments affect labor markets and human well-being, ensuring technology serves as a force for improvement rather than displacement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Recent Publications: White/Standard -->
      <section class="section-padding" data-particle-color="#E8EEF2" data-particle-speed="1">
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text-primary mb-12">Recent Publications</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-bg-surface/80 backdrop-blur-sm p-10 rounded-xl border border-border hover:border-border-hover transition-colors h-full flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h3 class="text-h3 text-text-primary mb-4">
              <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-024-81047-0" class="hover:text-flank transition-colors">
                Scientific Reports: Personality Prediction from Voice
              </a>
            </h3>
            <p class="text-body-large text-text-secondary mb-6">
              Our latest work published in Nature Portfolio's Scientific Reports demonstrates the validity of deep learning models in inferring Big Five personality traits from short audio clips.
            </p>
            <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-024-81047-0" class="text-flank font-semibold hover:underline text-body-large mt-auto">Read the paper â†’</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hidden md:block h-full">
            <img src="/images/photos/IMG_1091.jpg" alt="Martin Lukac presenting research" class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center rounded-2xl shadow-2xl" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Ongoing Research -->
      <section class="section-padding" data-particle-color="#E27B7B" data-particle-speed="0.6">
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text-primary mb-8">Ongoing Research</h2>
        <div class="bg-bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-xl border border-border">
          <h3 class="text-h3 text-text-primary mb-4">Passion vs. Pretense</h3>
          <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Investigating the interaction between passion expression and voice, specifically focusing on distinguishing authentic from faked passion. This is a collaborative project with <a href="https://kaikrautter.github.io/" class="text-flank hover:underline">Kai Krautter</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Selected Speaking -->
      <section class="pb-20" data-particle-color="#7EC699" data-particle-speed="0.4">
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text-primary mb-12">Selected Speaking</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <!-- 2025 -->
          <div class="group">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline gap-2 md:gap-8">
              <span class="text-flank font-mono font-medium min-w-[60px]">2025</span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-h4 text-text-primary group-hover:text-flank transition-colors">
                  <a href="https://www.oii.ox.ac.uk/" class="hover:underline">Oxford Internet Institute</a>
                </h3>
                <p class="text-body text-text-secondary mt-1">Start your own startup! workshop (Hosted by <a href="https://www.oii.ox.ac.uk/people/profiles/fabian-braesemann/" class="text-flank hover:underline">Fabian Braesemann</a>)</p>
              </div>
